    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "TLDR: `Host` is not the peer endpoint--it corresponds to the `Host` header in the HTTP request and to verify the endpoint's TLS certificate. It can be (and it more often than not is) `null`.\r\n\r\nSorry for the confusion: The documentation of the `Host` property probably needs to be clarified throughout the library (and not just in the interceptor API). I understand it might be a bit misleading.\r\n\r\n`Host` is `null` by default and only gets populated if one calls the `WithHost` property on the generated client, which is a class derived from `ClientBase<T>` and invokes its `WithHost(string host)` method, resulting in a new client instance that will populate the Host property in the interceptor chain and eventually set the `CallInvocationDetails.Host` property which will eventually get passed down to gRPC \r\n\r\nCore as the `host` argument to `grpc_channel_create_call`.\r\n(API: https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/e121fef19efdac51c20a4d0dab352b7ada387c72/include/grpc/grpc.h#L194 impl: \r\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a789ac30673f6e56960329e802bc199d5a9ac760/src/core/lib/surface/channel.cc#L312)\r\n\r\nThe host argument is mostly used to change the SSL target name for SNI and certificate validation purposes. c.f. https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/2635#issuecomment-126957809\r\n\r\n"
